oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Erwin place
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Erwin place, built in 1850. The home had a screened in front porch.
It has been torn down. The outside wall had brick six feet up on the inside. This is now the location of the J. J. Bell place.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses
